               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Sayr'nāmah by Sayyid Maḥmūd Bangālī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807 http://lccn.loc.gov/no2011159422 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85112612" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_912-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7534">Sayyid Maḥmūd Bangālī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="person_f7534">سيد محمود بنگالى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22201">Sayr'nāmah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_22201">سير نامه</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Substantial fragment from the account of the four-decade-long travels in the Middle East of the Ṣūfī saint, 
                <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658933.0x000001 viaf_91095241" role="subject">Abū ʿAbd Allāh Jalāl al-Dīn Ḥusayn ibn Aḥmad ibn Ḥusayn al-Bukhārī al-Ḥusaynī, known as the Makhdūm Jahāniyān Jahān Gasht</persName>(d. 785/1384), compiled under his supervision by his disciple, 
                <persName key="person_f7534" role="aut">Sayyid Maḥmūd Bangālī</persName>.
                        </p>
                        <p>Defective at the beginning, having lost several leaves from the opening preface.</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end.</p>
                        <p>Coarse nastaʿlīq.</p>
                        <p>Annotations.</p>
                        <p>Paper dust wrapper (BEIC legal publication on Act XXXVII of 1850); watermarked (standing sceptre lion in crowned oval frame; not dated); labels, torn, creased and stained.</p>
                        <p>Folios unbound, stained, torn, cropped, wormholes, later repairs.</p>
                        <p>Fragile.</p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
